    <summary type="html">&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Betrayer of Worlds&lt;/cite&gt;, by Larry Niven and Edward M. Lerner;
copyright 2010; ISBN 978-0-7653-6498-2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;aside class="admonition admonition-spoilers"&gt;
&lt;p class="admonition-title"&gt;Spoilers!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following discussion includes spoilers for this book.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/aside&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I like learning more of Louis Wu's background, but I thought pulling
him into the Puppeteer fleet, giving him a child, and kicking him
out with his memories removed, all before the events of Ringworld,
damaged my suspension of disbelief.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I thought the writing of this book was perfectly adequate, if not to
the standards of Niven in his prime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</summary>
